    "body": "NFC card is a very broad term which encompasses simple memory cards (not secure) to smartcards (secure). However there isn't a standard way to store keys and sign transactions etc, meaning there is no way to have a generic solution working on all cards. \r\n\r\nStatus supports Keycard which is an opensource applet and can run on any smartcard (NFC or not) that meets the requirements listed at https://keycard.tech/docs/applet_installation.html. We also distribute cards with Keycard preinstalled, based on NXP JCOP4 smartcards.",
